20inflammation%20informed%20my%20consuming%20this%20masala%20chai%2C%20which%20I%20now%20drink%20every%20single%20day%2C%26quot%3B%20H%C3%A9bert%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EH%C3%A9bert%20shared%20the%20chai%20tea%20recipe%20he%20makes%2C%20which%20is%20full%20of%20spices%2C%20including%20nutmeg%2C%20cardamon%2C%20ginger%2C%20cinnamon%2C%20and%20anise.%20%26quot%3BSpices%20are%20universally%20anti-inflammatory%2C%26quot%3B%20H%C3%A9bert%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20because%20spices%20contain%20antioxidants%20like%20phenolic%20compounds%20and%20flavonoids.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20credits%20the%20beverage%20for%20eliminating%20his%20need%20for%20nonsteroidal%20anti-inflammatory%20drugs%20(NSAIDs)%2C%20like%20ibuprofen%2C%20which%20can%20reduce%20inflammation.%20H%C3%A9bert%20said%20he%20hasn't%20used%20NSAIDs%20since%202011.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAdditionally%2C%20spices%20like%20cardamom%2C%20cinnamon%2C%20and%20nutmeg%20can%20make%20the%20drink%20taste%20sweeter%20than%20it%20actually%20is%2C%20according%20to%20H%C3%A9bert%2C%20making%20this%20a%20beverage%20that%20doesn't%20rely%20too%20heavily%20on%20added%20sweeteners.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEating%20a%20diet%20high%20in%20sugar%20can%20lead%20to%20inflammation.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fbest-place-to-get-a-chai-latte-review-2021-9%23it-was-pretty-spicy-which-helped-balance-all-the-sugar-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EPopular%20chai%20tea%20lattes%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20fast%20food%20chains%20can%20have%2030%20to%2050%20grams%20of%20sugar%20per%2012-ounce%20servings%20.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EConversely%2C%20H%C3%A9bert's%20recipe%20is%20sweetened%20with%20honey%2C%20and%20you%20can%20add%20as%20much%20or%20as%20little%20as%20you%20want.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EH%C3%A9bert's%20masala%20chai%20tea%20is%20flavorful%2C%20easy%20to%20make%2C%20and%20packs%20an%20anti-inflammatory%20punch.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere's%20how%20to%20make%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EIngredients%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20make%20one%20liter%20of%20chai%2C%20you%20will%20need%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3E1%20teaspoon%20of%20loose%20tea%20leaves%2F%20flakes%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3E1%E2%81%842%20teaspoon%20of%20ground%20cinnamon%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3E1%E2%81%844%20teaspoon%20of%20ground%20cardamom%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3E1%E2%81%844%20teaspoon%20of%20ground%20nutmeg%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3E1%E2%81%848%20teaspoon%20of%20ground%20coriander%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3E1%E2%81%842%20teaspoon%20of%20ground%20turmeric%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3E1%E2%81%842%20teaspoon%20of%20ground%20black%20pepper%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3E1%E2%81%844%20teaspoon%20whole%20(or%20ground)%20cloves%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3E2-3%20tablespoons%20of%20grated%20fresh%20ginger%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3E2-3%20tablespoons%20of%20honey%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3E%C2%BC%20to%20%C2%BD%20liter%20milk%20of%20choice%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20ground%20black%20pepper%20is%20an%20essential%20ingredient%2C%20since%20black%20pepper%20makes%20curcumin%2C%20the%20anti-inflammatory%20compound%20in%20turmeric%2C%20more%20bioavailable%20according%20to%20H%C3%A9bert.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EH%C3%A9bert%20said%20you%20can%20add%20other%20spices%20like%20anise%2C%20red%20or%20white%20pepper%2C%20vanilla%2C%20or%20anything%20else%20you%20think%20would%20enhance%20the%20flavor%20or%20anti-inflammatory%20capacity%20of%20the%20drink.%20You%20can%20also%20swap%20the%20fresh%20ginger%20for%20dried%20ginger%2C%20which%20is%20more%20potent%20%E2%80%94%20but%20H%C3%A9bert%20said%20he%20doesn't%20think%20it%20tastes%20as%20good.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20make%20the%20drink%2C%20H%C3%A9bert%20adds%20the%20tea%2C%20all%20the%20spices%2C%20and%20the%20fresh%20grated%20ginger%20into%20a%20large%20pot%20with%20one%20liter%20of%20boiling%20water.%20You%20can%20use%20two%20tea%20balls%20to%20hold%20the%20ingredients%20%E2%80%94%20one%20for%20the%20fresh%20ginger%2C%20and%20one%20for%20all%20the%20other%20spices%20and%20tea.%20Alternatively%2C%20you%20can%20just%20add%20all%20the%20ingredients%20to%20the%20water%20and%20strain%20them%20out%20afterwards.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EH%C3%A9bert%20lets%20everything%20steep%20together%20for%205%20minutes.%20If%20you%20like%2C%20you%20can%20let%20the%20tea%20steep%20for%20longer%2C%20which%20will%20create%20a%20stronger%20flavor%20and%20more%20potent%20anti-inflammatory%20effect.%20Then%20add%20in%20the%20honey%20and%20milk.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20ready%2C%20pour%20into%20a%20cup%20and%20enjoy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20recipe%20makes%20about%20four%2012-ounce%20servings.%20You%20can%20store%20any%20leftover%20tea%20in%20the%20fridge.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftea-recipe-preventing-reducing-inflammation-pain-2023-12%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701987182000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65720e7d0ec98e92f74d3572%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftea-recipe-preventing-reducing-inflammation-pain-2023-12%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Dr.%20James%20H%C3%A9bert%20has%20dedicated%20his%20career%20to%20studying%20inflammation.%20H%C3%A9bert%20shares%20his%20anti-inflammatory%20masala%20chai%20tea%20recipe%2C%20which%20he%20drinks%20every%20day.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22khull%40insider.com%20(Kate%20Hull)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A9%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftea-recipe-preventing-reducing-inflammation-pain-2023-12%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Prose%20vs.%20Function%20of%20Beauty%20%E2%80%94%20which%20of%20these%20popular%20custom%20haircare%20companies%20should%20you%20try%3F%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EWhen%20you%20buy%20through%20our%20links%2C%20Insider%20may%20earn%20an%2