2%25E2%2580%25AFPM.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESometimes%2C%20I%20think%20about%20how%20Zoya%20Akhtar%E2%80%99s%20career%20would%20have%20turned%20out%20if%20her%20directorial%20debut%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ELuck%20By%20Chance%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20(2009)%2C%20had%20done%20well%20at%20the%20box%20office.%20A%20film%20that%20Akhtar%20wrote%20and%20dreamt%20about%20making%20for%20nearly%20a%20decade%2C%20was%20so%20assured%20even%20in%20its%20silences%20that%20it%20probably%20became%20an%20unfair%20yardstick%20for%20each%20of%20her%20successive%20films.%20After%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ELuck%20By%20Chance%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20most%20of%20her%20films%20have%20had%20glimpses%20of%20the%20nifty%20touch%20but%20it%E2%80%99s%20also%20been%20easy%20to%20spot%20the%20compromises%20she%E2%80%99s%20made%20to%20make%20sure%20the%20film%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20%E2%80%98flop%E2%80%99%20like%20her%20debut.%20Whether%20it%E2%80%99s%20the%20obvious%20casting%20of%20Katrina%20Kaif%20sounding%20like%20a%20self-help%20book%20in%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EZindagi%20Na%20Milegi%20Dobara%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20(2011)%2C%20the%20drawn-out%2C%20insipid%20climax%20of%20the%20otherwise%20observant%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EDil%20Dhadakne%20Do%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20(2015)%2C%20or%20even%20the%20feel-good%2C%20corporate-tested%20journey%20afforded%20to%20a%20Muslim%20hip-hop%20sensation%20from%20the%20wrong%20side%20of%20the%20tracks%20in%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ffilm%2Fgully-boy-movie-review%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EGully%20Boy%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20(2019)%2C%20each%20Akhtar%20film%20has%20felt%20more%20accommodating%20than%20the%20last.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFrom%20being%20someone%20who%20trusted%20the%20audience%20to%20read%20between%20the%20lines%20in%20her%20debut%2C%20like%20that%20astoundingly-performed%20first%20scene%20between%20Alyy%20Khan%20and%20Konkona%20Sen%20Sharma%20%E2%80%93%20which%20goes%20from%20parody%20to%20somewhere%20dark%20in%20less%20than%20a%20minute%20%E2%80%93%20Akhtar%2C%20in%20her%20latest%20film%20called%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Archies%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20(based%20on%20the%20famous%20American%20comics%20of%20the%20same%20name)%2C%20has%20included%20a%20song%20called%20%E2%80%98Everything%20is%20Politics%E2%80%99.%20Written%20probably%20to%20wake%20a%20South%20Bombay%20brat%20out%20of%20their%20slumber%20to%20become%20socially%20conscious%2C%20the%20song%20pretty%20much%20distils%20the%20problems%20with%20Akhtar%E2%80%99s%20latest%20film.%20The%20intentions%20are%20pure%20and%20there%E2%80%99s%20an%20idealism%20permeating%20through%20it%2C%20but%20the%20song%20(like%20the%20film)%20takes%20place%20in%20such%20a%20cocoon%20of%20privilege%20that%20it%E2%80%99s%20hard%20to%20take%20seriously%20beyond%20a%20point.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22allowfullscreen%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2F07zwmOypaV8%3Fsi%3DaxXzxfueezlIGcMK%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22100%25%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22504%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%20data-mce-type%3D%5C%22bookmark%5C%22%3E%EF%BB%BF%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAkhtar%E2%80%99s%20adaptation%20is%20set%20in%20a%20fictitious%20British-Indian%20hill%20station%20(presumably%20in%20Northern%20India)%20called%20Riverdale%2C%20in%201964.%20Just%20like%20the%20comics%2C%20the%20tone%20of%20the%20film%20feels%20Utopian%2C%20where%20everyone%20acts%20in%20good%20faith%2C%20including%20the%20antagonist.%20The%20performances%20seem%20deliberately%20high-pitched%2C%20drawing%20attention%20to%20their%20theatricality.%20Most%20characters%20embody%20one-note%20tropes%2C%20which%20is%20the%20cornerstone%20for%20writing%20about%20groups%20(like%20the%20sitcom%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EFriends%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E)%20to%20love%20triangles%20(like%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EKuch%20Kuch%20Hota%20Hai%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E).%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E17-year-old%20Archie%20Andrews%20(Agastya%20Nanda)%2C%20apart%20from%20being%20in%20high%20school%2C%20works%20in%20his%20father%E2%80%99s%20travel%20agency%20and%20is%20the%20lead%20singer%20for%20his%20band%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Archies%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20Betty%20Cooper%20(Khushi%20Kapoor)%20is%20the%20girl%20next%20door%20who%20is%20overly%20caring%20and%20generous%20to%20people%20around%20her.%20Veronica%20Lodge%20(Suhana%20Khan)%20is%20Riverdale%E2%80%99s%20vivacious%20prom%20queen%2C%20daughter%20of%20the%20industrialist%20Mr%20Lodge%20(Alyy%20Khan)%20%E2%80%93%20the%20man%20behind%20the%20plan%20to%20tear%20down%20the%20town%E2%80%99s%20centrally%20located%20park%20to%20build%20a%20hotel.%20The%20screenplay%20(written%20by%20Ayesha%20Devitre%20Dhillon%2C%20Reema%20Kagti%20and%20Akhtar)%20introduces%20obstacles%20in%20every%20other%20scene%2C%20only%20to%20resolve%20them%20swiftly.%20It%E2%80%99s%20a%20death%20knell%20for%20any%20film%2C%20when%20the%20%E2%80%98rules%E2%80%99%20of%20the%20world%20suggest%20that%20anything%20goes%2C%20or%20nothing%20matters.%20It%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20matter%20what%20anyone%20does%20after%20this%2C%20we%E2%80%99re%20headed%20towards%20the%20rainbow%20of%20%E2%80%98happily%20ever%20after%E2%80%99%20soon%20enough.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESuzanne%20Caplan%20Merwanji%E2%80%99s%20immaculate%20production%20design%20and%20Dhara%20Jain%E2%80%99s%20precise%20set%20decoration%20reminded%20me%20of%20Greta%20Gerwig%E2%80%99s%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EBarbie%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20There%E2%80%99s%20a%20deliberate%20falseness%20to%20the%20surroundings%2C%20to%20make%20it%20look%20like%20we%E2%80%99re%20inside%20a%20comic%20strip.%20However%2C%20while%20Gerwig%20used%20the%20world%20of%20the%20film%20to%20ask%20more%20pressing%20questions%20of%20it%2C%20Akhtar%20is%20relatively%20less%20successful.%20There%20are%20flourishes%20of%20%E2%80%98revisionism%E2%80%99%20%E2%80%93%20where%20Veronica%20and%20Betty%20confront%20Archie%20about%20his%20%E2%80%98confusion%E2%80%99%2C%20or%20how%20Reggie%20(Vedang%20Raina)%2C%20the%20jock%20of%20the%20group%2C%20is%20shown%20to%20be%20the%20most%20sensitive.%20There%20are%20real-world%20allusions%20to%20the%20free%20press%2C%20the%20independence%20struggle%20in%201947%2C%20and%20capitalism%20trumping%20all-round%20development%2C%20but%20they%20all%20feel%20mostly%20incidental%20by%20the%20end.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThere%20also%20seems%20to%20be%20an%20overwhelming%20naivete%20that%20seems%20to%20be%20drilled%20into%20most%20of%20the%20characters%2C%20including%20the%20elders%20in%20the%20town.%20When%20bookseller%20Hal%20Cooper%E2%80%99s%20(Satyajit%20Sharma)%20shop%20is%20overrun%20so%20that%20the%20town%20can%20have%20its%20plaza%20%E2%80%93%20he%E2%80%99s%20tensed%20about%20it%20in%20one%20moment%2C%20and%20joyous%20about%20landing%20a%20job%20as%20an%20assistant%20manager%20at%20the%20store%20of%20his%20corporate%20rival%20in%20the%20next.%20Later%2C%20he%20refuses%20to%20sign%20a%20petition%20against%20the%20razing%20down%20of%20the%20park%20for%20Mr%20Lodge%E2%80%99s%20hotel%20%E2%80%93%20because%20he%20considers%20it%20would%20not%20be%20gracious%20on%20his%20part.%20I%20realise%20what%20Akhtar%20is%20trying%20to%20do%20here%2C%20but%20it%20works%20more%20in%20theory.%20In%20a%20different%20scene%20between%20Veronica%20and%20Mr%20Lodge%20%E2%80%93%20he%20questions%20her%20about%20her%20convenient%20activism%20to%20not%20lose%20face%20in%20front%20of%20friends%2C%20even%20though%20she%E2%80%99s%20never%20had%20a%20question%20about%20how%20her%20father%20earns%20the%20riches%20she%E2%80%99s%20happy%20to%20splurge%20otherwise.%20It%E2%80%99s%20a%20fine%20moment%20that%20could%E2%80%99ve%20prompted%20introspection%20in%20Veronica%2C%20which%20could%E2%80%99ve%20also%20doubled%20up%20as%20a%20meta-commentary%20on%20Suhana%20Khan%20being%20forced%20to%20introspect%20about%20being%20the%20daughter%20of%20the%20most%20famous%20film%20star%20in%20the%20world.%20Alas%2C%20the%20moment%20is%20left%20hanging%20in%20the%20air.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOut%20of%20the%20cast%2C%20only%20Vedang%20Raina%20and%20Aditi%20Saigal%20(Dot)%20seem%20to%20exhibit%20sparks%20of%20spontaneity.%20Khushi%20Kapoor%20as%20Betty%20is%20adorable%20as%20someone%20who%20spends%20a%20large%20part%20of%20her%20screen%20time%20looking%20longingly%20at%20Archie%2C%20but%20that%E2%80%99s%20about%20it.%20Mihir%20Ahuja%20plays%20%E2%80%98Jughead%E2%80%99%20Jones%20with%20an%20exaggerated%20awkwardness%2C%20as%20the%20ever-hungry%20chap%2C%20with%20a%20firm%20grip%20on%20right%20and%20wrong.%20Nanda%20and%20Khan%2C%20both%2C%20seem%20too%20aware%20of%20the%20camera%20to%20treat%20their%20performances%20as%20anything%20other%20than%20an%20extension%20of%20their%20real-life%20personas%20around%20mobile%20phones%20or%20the%20paparazzi.%20Everything%20is%20too%20groomed%2C%20and%20every%20word%20(dialogues%20by%20Farhan%20Akhtar)%20coming%20out%20of%20their%20mouth%20feels%20air-brushed.%20These%20young%20actors%20are%20earnest%2C%20but%20they%20also%20seem%20too%20boot-camped%2C%20though%20it%20might%20not%20be%20fair%20to%20fully%20judge%20their%20acting%20potential%20on%20this%20one%20film%20alone.%20Among%20the%20supporting%20cast%2C%20Puja%20Sarup%20%E2%80%93%20a%20member%20of%20the%20Riverdale%20council%2C%20who%20pilfers%20the%20biscuits%20in%20a%20tissue%20at%20the%20end%20of%20every%20council%20meeting%20%E2%80%93%20is%20the%20only%20one%20who%20makes%20an%20impression.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Archies%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20is%20surely%20not%20Zoya%20Akhtar%E2%80%99s%20finest%20hour.%20It%E2%80%99s%20a%20mollycoddled%20ode%20to%20a%20bygone%20era%2C%20a%20frothy%20concoction%20pandering%20to%20its%20audience.%20The%20world-building%2C%20the%20songs%20and%20the%20set-pieces%20are%20nicely%20done%2C%20but%20not%20enough%20to%20make%20this%20143-minute%20film%20feel%20any%20tighter%20and%20shorter.%20It%E2%80%99s%20also%20a%20sign%20of%20our%20times%20that%20something%20even%20slightly%20topical%20or%20rebellious%20needs%20to%20be%20buried%20so%20deep%20into%20a%20world%2C%20surrounded%20by%20distractions%20that%20it%20makes%20the%20commentary%20almost%20ineffective.%20As%20any%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ELuck%20By%20Chance%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20fan%20would%20attest%20to%20%E2%80%93%20this%20is%20the%20most%20pliant%20Akhtar%20has%20ever%20been.%20So%2C%20looking%20at%20the%20bright%20side%2C%20the%20only%20way%20from%20here%20is%20up.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701959361000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F07191933%2FScreenshot-2023-12-07-at-7.18.42%25E2%2580%25AFPM.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ffilm%2Fthe-archies-zoya-akhtar-review%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20world-building%2C%20the%20songs%20and%20the%20set-pieces%20are%20nicely%20done%2C%20but%20not%20enough%20to%20make%20this%20143-minute%20film%20feel%20any%20tighter%20and%20shorter.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ffilm%2Fthe-archies-zoya-akhtar-review%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Trump%20criticism%20takes%20center%20stage%20amid%20intra-party%20strife%20in%20GOP%20debate%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701958359000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-105817722%2Cimgsize-45050.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Ftrump-criticism-takes-center-stage-as-gop-presidential-hopefuls-wrestle-with-haleys-rising-popularity%2Farticleshow%2F105817421.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F105817421.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3EThe%20Republican%20presidential%20debate%20in%20Alabama%20saw%20former%20UN%20Ambassador%20Nikki%20Haley%20face%20scrutiny%20from%20fellow%20candidates%20Ron%20DeSantis%20and%20Vivek%20Ramaswamy.%20DeSantis%20accused%20Haley%20of%20not%20supporting%20a%20ban%20on%20gender-affirming%20medical%20care%20for%20transgender%20youth.%20Ramaswamy%20targeted%20her%20with%20corruption%20accusations.%20Haley%20defended%20herself%20and%20mocked%20her%20rivals.%20Meanwhile%2C%20former%20Governor%20Chris%20Christie%20criticized%20candidates%20for%20not%20taking%20on%20absent%20front-runner%20Donald%20Trump.%20The%20debate%20revealed%20divisions%20within%20the%20party%20regarding%20Trump%2C%20and%20candidates%20are%20aware%20of%20the%20need%20for%20a%20breakout%20moment%20in%20the%20upcoming%20Iowa%20caucuses.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TOI%20World%20Desk%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Ftrump-criticism-takes-center-stage-as-gop-presidential-hopefuls-wrestle-with-haleys-rising-popularity%2Farticleshow%2F105817421.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Forced%20to%20Pull%20Story%20on%20Indian%20Firm's%20Alleged%20Global%20Hacking%20Operation%2C%20Reuters%20to%20Fight%20Court%20Order%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F07184417%2F2493267536_f12b7eef35_h.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Following%20a%20Delhi%20court%E2%80%99s%20preliminary%20order%2C%20the%20news%20agency%20Reuters%20has%20temporarily%20removed%20a%20special%20investigation%20which%20claimed%20that%20an%20Indian%20information%20technology%20company%2C%20Appin%2C%20stole%20data%20from%20prominent%20persons%20around%20the%20globe%2C%20including%20politicians%2C%20military%20officials%20and%20business%20executives.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EReuters%2C%20however%2C%20said%20that%20it%20%E2%80%9Cstands%20by%20its%20reporting%20and%20plans%20to%20appeal%20the%20decision.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20additional%20district%20judge%20North%20West%20Rohini%20court%20found%20the%20article%20to%20be%20%3Cem%3Eprima%20facie%3C%2Fem%3E%20%E2%80%9Cindicative%20of%20defamation%2C%E2%80%9D%20according%20to%20a%20copy%20of%20the%20order%20seen%20by%20The%20Wire.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20special%20report%20was%20published%20on%20November%2016%2C%202023%20and%20was%20titled%2C%20%E2%80%98How%20an%20Indian%20Startup%20Hacked%20the%20World%E2%80%99.%20It%20claimed%20that%20the%20Delhi-based%20firm%20Appin%2C%20which%20was%20started%20by%20brothers%20Rajat%20and%20Anuj%20Khare%2C%20allegedly%20hacked%20on%20an%20industrial%20scale%2C%20stealing%20data%20from%20political%20leaders%2C%20international%20executives%2C%20prominent%20attorneys%20and%20more.%20Reuters%20described%20its%20activity%20as%20a%20%E2%80%9Csprawling%20cyber-mercenary%20operation%20that%20extended%20across%20the%20world.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Finvestigates%2Fspecial-report%2Fusa-hackers-appin%2F%5C%22%3EEditor%E2%80%99s%20note%3C%2Fa%3E%20published%20on%20December%205%2C%20Reuters%20said%20it%20had%20temporarily%20removed%20the%20article%20to%20comply%20with%20a%20preliminary%20court%20order%20issued%20on%20December%204.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20order%2C%20additional%20district%20judge%20Rakesh%20Kumar%20Singh%20noted%20that%20he%20was%20prima%20facie%20satisfied%20that%20the%20special%20report%20was%20%E2%80%9Cindicative%20of%20defamation%2C%E2%80%9D%20and%20that%20the%20website%20should%20not%20retain%20such%20an%20article%20in%20the%20public%20domain.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%2C%20however%2C%20clarified%20that%20this%20was%20only%20a%20prima%20facie%20opinion.%20The%20%E2%80%9Cdefendants%20shall%20have%20sufficient%20opportunity%20to%20express%20their%20views%20through%20reply%2C%20contest%20in%20the%20main%20suit%20etc.%20and%20the%20final%20decision%20shall%20be%20taken%20subsequently.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20order%20was%20issued%20amid%20a%20pending%20lawsuit%20brought%20against%20Reuters%20in%20November%202022%20by%20the%20lawyers%20of%20Appin%20Association%20of%20Training%20Centre%2C%20accusing%20the%20news%20agency%20of%20a%20defamatory%20campaign.%20%E2%80%9CAs%20set%20forth%20in%20its%20court%20filings%2C%20Reuters%20disputes%20those%20claims%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20agency%20stated.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Reuters%20report%20claimed%20its%20investigation%20found%20that%20Appin%20grew%20from%20an%20educational%20startup%20to%20%E2%80%9Ca%20hack-for-hire%20powerhouse%E2%80%9D.%20Appin%20alumni%20went%20on%20to%20form%20other%20firms%20that%20are%20still%20active%2C%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20said%20that%20Khare%20was%20a%2020-year-old%20computer%20science%20student%20when%20he%20and%20his%20friends%20came%20up%20with%20the%20idea%20for%20Appin%20in%202003.%20They%20launched%20their%20first%20classes%20on%20computer%20programming.%20By%202005%2C%20the%20company%20had%20an%20office%20in%20west%20Delhi.%20Soon%2C%20he%20took%20charge%20of%20the%20firm%20with%20his%20brother%20Anuj%2C%20a%20motivational%20speaker%20who%20returned%20to%20India%20after%20a%20stint%20running%20a%20startup%20in%20Texas%2C%20Reuters%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERajat%20Khare%E2%80%99s%20US%20representative%2C%20the%20law%20firm%20Clare%20Locke%2C%20rejected%20any%20association%20between%20its%20client%20and%20the%20cyber-mercenary%20business.%20It%20told%20Reuters%20that%20Khare%20%E2%80%9Chas%20never%20operated%20or%20supported%2C%20and%20certainly%20did%20not%20create%2C%20any%20illegal%20%E2%80%98hack%20for%20hire%E2%80%99%20industry%20in%20India%20or%20anywhere%20else.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EClare%20Locke%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CMr.%20Khare%20has%20dedicated%20much%20of%20his%20career%20to%20the%20fields%20of%20information%20technology%20security%20%E2%80%93%20that%20is%2C%20cyber-defense%20and%20the%20prevention%20of%20illicit%20hacking.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EReuters%20noted%20that%20while%20the%20original%20Appin%20has%20now%20largely%20disappeared%20from%20public%20view%20its%20impact%20was%20still%20felt%20today%2C%20as%20copycat%20firms%20led%20by%20its%20alumni%20continue%20to%20target%20thousands.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKhare%E2%80%99s%20lawyers%20said%20media%20articles%20tying%20him%20to%20hacking%20were%20%E2%80%9Cfalse%E2%80%9D%20or%20%E2%80%9Cfundamentally%20flawed.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EClare%20Locke%2C%20as%20quoted%20in%20the%20report%2C%20said%20under%20Khare%E2%80%99s%20tenure%2C%20Appin%20specialised%20in%20training%20thousands%20of%20students%20in%20cybersecurity%2C%20robotics%20and%20artificial%20intelligence%2C%20%E2%80%9Cnever%20in%20illicit%20hacking.%E2%80%9D%20The%20lawyers%20said%20Khare%20left%20Appin%2C%20in%20part%2C%20because%20rogue%20actors%20were%20operating%20under%20the%20company%E2%80%99s%20brand%2C%20and%20he%20wanted%20%E2%80%9Cto%20avoid%20the%20appearance%20of%20associations%20with%20people%20who%20were%20misusing%20the%20Appin%20name.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Delhi%20district%20judge%2C%20while%20ordering%20Reuters%20to%20take%20down%20the%20article%2C%20said%20the%20%E2%80%9Cbalance%20of%20convenience%E2%80%9D%20lies%20in%20directing%20the%20withdrawal%20of%20the%20content.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20am%20of%20the%20opinion%20that%20even%20if%20the%20defendants%20for%20some%20period%20do%20not%20retain%20the%20article%20on%20the%20website%20and%20on%20that%20account%20they%20suffer%20any%20market%20value%2C%20%5Bthey%5D%20can%20be%20ultimately%20compensated%20by%20money%20from%20the%20plaintiff%20but%20the%20retention%20of%20such%20material%20on%20the%20website%20if%20allowed%2C%20the%20same%20may%20have%20devastating%20effect%20on%20the%20general%20students%20population%20of%20India%20(sic)%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20court%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EReuters%20said%20its%20report%20on%20Appin%20was%20based%20on%20thousands%20of%20company%20emails%20as%20well%20as%20financial%20records%2C%20presentations%2C%20photos%20and%20instant%20messages%20from%20the%20firm.%20Reporters%20also%20reviewed%20case%20files%20from%20American%2C%20Norwegian%2C%20Dominican%20and%20Swiss%20law%20enforcement%2C%20and%20interviewed%20dozens%20of%20former%20Appin%20employees%20and%20hundreds%20of%20victims%20of%20India-based%20hackers%2C%20it%20said.%20The%20reporters%20gathered%20the%20material%20%E2%80%93%20which%20spans%202005%20until%20earlier%20this%20year%20%E2%80%93%20from%20ex-employees%2C%20clients%20and%20security%20professionals%20who%E2%80%99ve%20studied%20the%20company%2C%20the%20agency%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EReuters%20said%20it%20verified%20the%20authenticity%20of%20the%20Appin%20communications%20with%2015%20people%2C%20including%20private%20investigators%20who%20commissioned%20hacks%20and%20ex-Appin%20hackers%20themselves.%20The%20news%20agency%20also%20asked%20US%20cybersecurity%20firm%20SentinelOne%20to%20review%20the%20material%20for%20signs%20that%20it%20had%20been%20digitally%20altered.%20The%20firm%20said%20it%20found%20none%2C%20according%20to%20the%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701957613000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F07184417%2F2493267536_f12b7eef35_h.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fdelhi-court-reuters-takes-down-story-indian-firm-hacking%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20additional%20district%20judge%20North%20West%20Rohini%20court%20found%20the%20article%20to%20be%20prima%20facie%20%E2%80%9Cindicative%20of%20defamation%E2%80%9D.%22%2C%22author