-foreign-policy-192977%5C%22%3EHenry%20Kissinger%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20the%20chief%20guest.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBy%20then%2C%20a%20quarter%20century%20had%20passed%20since%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.npr.org%2F2023%2F09%2F10%2F1193755188%2Fchile-coup-50-years-pinochet-kissinger-human-rights-allende%5C%22%3Emilitary%20coup%20that%20toppled%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20democratically%20elected%20Chilean%20President%20Salvador%20Allende%20%E2%80%93%20an%20event%20that%20gave%20rise%20to%20General%20Augusto%20Pinochet%E2%80%99s%20brutal%2017-year-long%20military%20dictatorship%20%E2%80%93%20but%20the%20issue%20still%20lingered.%20Many%20Chileans%20bitterly%20remembered%20the%20role%20of%20the%20US%20government%2C%20and%20of%20Kissinger%20in%20particular%2C%20in%20the%20breakdown%20of%20Chilean%20democracy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20something%20Kissinger%20himself%20acknowledged%20during%20that%20dinner%20%E2%80%93%20which%20I%20did%20attend%2C%20just%20late%20due%20to%20encountering%20a%20hailstorm.%20Kissinger%20explained%20that%20he%20always%20declined%20invitations%20to%20visit%20my%20home%20country%20out%20of%20fear%20over%20what%20%E2%80%9CAllende%20Chileans%E2%80%9D%20would%20do%20to%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPlenty%20of%20Chileans%20still%20despise%20Kissinger.%20On%20news%20of%20his%20death%20at%20the%20age%20of%20100%20on%20November%2029%2C%202023%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fjg_valdes%2Fstatus%2F1730066974116323584%5C%22%3EJuan%20Gabriel%20Valdes%2C%20Chile%E2%80%99s%20ambassador%20to%20the%20US%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20summed%20up%20that%20sentiment%20when%20he%20posted%20in%20Spanish%20on%20X%2C%20the%20platform%20previously%20known%20as%20Twitter%3A%20%E2%80%9CA%20man%20has%20died%20whose%20historical%20brilliance%20never%20managed%20to%20conceal%20his%20profound%20moral%20misery.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%E2%80%99s%20hard%20to%20overestimate%20the%20role%20Kissinger%20played%20in%20Chile.%20As%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%